snippet.textDisplay: For the Meghan situation, something sh*t with YouTube happened to me! I was doing well with my channel. I had 350 subscribers, finally growing a small audience. One day I open Discord and my friend says, "Dude, where's your channel?" I looked and they fudging terminated my channel. I tried to reach out to YouTube for WEEKS. Months later, my dad found out it was for copyright issues. I tried to get my channel back one more time, basically saying, "Hey! I'm 13, I just had my own channel, I didn't know this would happen. You guys never told me to stop, nobody ever took my videos down." They just removed my channel AND the Google account associated, which had everything I've ever done on my computer, without giving me a warning or taking down my videos. The moral of the story, Netflix isn't a joke, YouTube is.
